## When to Use Each Approach

### 1. Use existing variables directly (preferred)

```css
.card {
  padding: var(--padding);
  margin: var(--margin);
  gap: var(--xxs);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius);
  border: var(--border);
}
```

### 2. Use calc() with variables (for custom sizes)

```css
.special-card {
  padding: calc(var(--padding) * 2);
  width: calc(var(--xl) * 1.5);
  gap: calc(var(--xxs) * 3);
  border-radius: calc(var(--border-radius) * 2);
}
```

### 3. Hardcoded values (ONLY with explicit justification)

```css
.icon {
  /* Rare exception: Icon assets are exactly 24px and can't scale */
  width: 24px;
  height: 24px;
}
```

## ❌ WRONG - Don't do this

```css
.card {
  padding: 16px;        /* ❌ Use var(--padding) */
  margin: 24px;         /* ❌ Use var(--margin) */
  gap: 8px;             /* ❌ Use var(--xxs) or calc(var(--xxs) * 2) */
  border-radius: 12px;  /* ❌ Use var(--border-radius) */
  width: 400px;         /* ❌ Use var(--xl) or calc() */
}
```

## ✅ RIGHT - Do this

```css
.card {
  padding: var(--padding);
  margin: var(--margin);
  gap: calc(var(--xxs) * 2);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius);
  width: var(--xl);
}
```

## Color Variables

**ALL colors must use CSS variables from `styles/variables.css`:**

- Never use hex codes (#ffffff), rgb(), or rgba() directly
- Use semantic color variables: `--color-white`, `--color-neutral-*`, `--color-blue-*`, `--color-red-*`, `--color-green-*`, etc.

**❌ WRONG:**

```css
.button {
  background: #069bfa;
  color: #ffffff;
  border: 1px solid #424242;
}
```

**✅ RIGHT:**

```css
.button {
  background: var(--color-blue-500);
  color: var(--color-white);
  border: var(--border-width) var(--border-style) var(--color-neutral-800);
}
```

## Component-Scoped Variables

Allow component-scoped variables for complex calculations:

```css
.progress-bar {
  --progress-width: 0%;
  --progress-color: var(--color-primary);

  width: 100%;
  height: 8px;
  background: var(--color-background);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius);
}

.progress-bar-fill {
  width: var(--progress-width);
  height: 100%;
  background: var(--progress-color);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius);
  transition: width var(--run) var(--fadein);
}
```

**Component:**

```tsx
<div className="progress-bar">
  <div
    className="progress-bar-fill"
    style={{ '--progress-width': `${progress}%` } as React.CSSProperties}
  />
</div>
```

## Quick Reference

### Spacing Scale

- `--xxs` → 0.25rem (4px)
- `--xs` → 1rem (16px)
- `--padding` → calculated from xs
- `--margin` → calculated from xs
- `--tile` → 4rem (64px)
- `--xl` → 16rem (256px)
- `--xxl` → 64rem (1024px)

### Common Patterns

```css
/* Spacing */
padding: var(--padding);
margin: var(--margin);
gap: var(--xxs);

/* Doubled/Tripled */
padding: calc(var(--padding) * 2);
gap: calc(var(--xxs) * 3);

/* Borders */
border: var(--border);
border-radius: var(--border-radius);

/* Colors */
color: var(--color-neutral-900);
background: var(--background);
border-color: var(--border-color);

/* Transitions */
transition: all var(--run) var(--fadein);
transition: opacity var(--run) var(--fadein);
```

## Remember

- **Spacing/Sizing:** Use CSS variables or calc() - NEVER hardcoded pixels
- **Colors:** Use CSS variables - NEVER hex codes or rgb()
- **Consistency:** Using the design system creates visual harmony
- **Maintainability:** Variables can be updated globally in one place
